10/04/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The beating of a soldier at the Goce Delcev military barracks in Skopje has cost the commander of the barracks his job.
Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski decided on Wednesday (9 April) to sack Col Stojce Deskovski, who also serves as dean of the military academy.
Witnesses say Pt Sali Krasniqi was beaten for 30 minutes Monday evening by three drunken civilians.
(Utrisnki Vesnik, Dnevnik - 10/04/03;
MIA, Makfax, A1 TV - 09/04/03)
